1
00:00:11,533 --> 00:00:15,800
Forgive me for giving you up
when you were just a baby.

2
00:00:15,867 --> 00:00:17,733
Olive is indeed my sister.

3
00:00:17,800 --> 00:00:19,667
You hurt me a lot, Mommy.

4
00:00:19,733 --> 00:00:23,367
And I don't deserve to get hurt
and imprisoned in this house.

5
00:00:23,433 --> 00:00:25,900
I want to be free,
I want to be strong,

6
00:00:25,967 --> 00:00:27,433
and I want to be happy.

7
00:00:27,500 --> 00:00:31,000
I think it's my fault
that she became like that.

8
00:00:31,067 --> 00:00:32,567
I gave them away.

9
00:00:32,633 --> 00:00:37,567
I hope someday you and your
siblings will get along.

10
00:00:37,667 --> 00:00:39,833
I think I know where we can find
them.

11
00:00:39,900 --> 00:00:41,567
She could have taken Mookie
there!

12
00:00:41,633 --> 00:00:43,500
Where are you going?

13
00:00:43,567 --> 00:00:45,367
Are you trying to escape?

14
00:00:45,433 --> 00:00:46,433
Mommy...

15
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:48,433
Don't you even call me "Mommy'!

16
00:00:50,233 --> 00:00:51,433
Hurry!

17
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:55,900
A disobedient brat like you
deserves to be punished!

18
00:01:30,933 --> 00:01:32,300
Are they here?

19
00:01:32,367 --> 00:01:33,167
Emma?

20
00:01:33,233 --> 00:01:34,300
They're not here.

21
00:01:35,400 --> 00:01:40,500
Wait, I think we've been fooled
again.

22
00:01:42,833 --> 00:01:44,867
Mookie's not here.

23
00:01:44,933 --> 00:01:46,300
Where can they be?

24
00:01:47,500 --> 00:01:50,300
We looked and called everywhere,
but they were not here.

25
00:02:02,567 --> 00:02:03,933
Stop crying, Mookie.

26
00:02:06,833 --> 00:02:08,833
We have to rejoice.

27
00:02:10,033 --> 00:02:10,800
Because...

28
00:02:12,067 --> 00:02:14,533
Do you know where we're going?

29
00:02:20,533 --> 00:02:23,233
We're going to a beautiful
place.

30
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:27,033
We're going to paradise.

31
00:02:28,767 --> 00:02:31,900
Where there won't be anymore
tears.

32
00:02:31,967 --> 00:02:36,100
No more tears, Mookie.

33
00:02:42,500 --> 00:02:44,000
And I promise you,

34
00:02:48,967 --> 00:02:50,800
we will be happy.

35
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:55,433
We'll be together.

36
00:02:55,500 --> 00:03:00,733
And we will live happily ever
after.

37
00:03:15,833 --> 00:03:19,933
Based on your report, we can
file a case of kidnapping,

38
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:23,567
child abuse, physical injury,
and frustrated murder.

39
00:03:23,667 --> 00:03:27,733
Officer, if Olive faces
all those cases against her,

40
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:31,367
does that mean she will go to
prison?

41
00:03:31,433 --> 00:03:33,000
Yes, that's right.

42
00:03:35,700 --> 00:03:38,000
She deserves to go to prison.

43
00:03:38,067 --> 00:03:39,567
She can rot in there.

44
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:45,033
That means we can finally
get justice, Emma.

45
00:03:46,367 --> 00:03:49,967
I know that Olive deserves
to get punished

46
00:03:50,033 --> 00:03:51,867
for what she'd done.

47
00:03:51,933 --> 00:03:52,567
But...

48
00:03:53,967 --> 00:03:56,267
what if she gets a grave
sentence?

49
00:03:56,333 --> 00:03:58,767
What if she gets life
imprisonment?

50
00:04:00,267 --> 00:04:05,333
And what if I get sick?
I'm already old. What if I die?

51
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:07,500
Will I die without being able
to be with her?

52
00:04:07,567 --> 00:04:08,967
Mom,

53
00:04:09,033 --> 00:04:12,933
we must accept any punishment
that may be given to her.

54
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:15,300
No matter how grave it is.

55
00:04:15,367 --> 00:04:17,900
Don't you feel anything for her?

56
00:04:19,267 --> 00:04:20,933
You're not worried?

57
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:22,300
Nothing?

58
00:04:24,300 --> 00:04:25,700
Even as her sister?

59
00:04:25,767 --> 00:04:30,533
Let's say I can accept Olive
as my sister.

60
00:04:30,633 --> 00:04:35,467
But I can't forget her cruelty
to my daughter.

61
00:04:38,633 --> 00:04:41,400
Ligaya, Emma.

62
00:04:42,633 --> 00:04:47,467
I think we should talk about
this later.

63
00:04:47,533 --> 00:04:51,100
We have to find Olive
so she can take accountability

64
00:04:51,167 --> 00:04:54,500
for what she's done.

65
00:04:55,667 --> 00:04:58,733
You said that you've searched
all her properties.

66
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:01,767
Yes, we did.

67
00:05:01,867 --> 00:05:04,600
We went to all our family's
properties.

68
00:05:04,667 --> 00:05:07,300
But we didn't find her.

69
00:05:07,367 --> 00:05:10,433
Perhaps you know someone we can
ask about her whereabouts.

70
00:05:10,500 --> 00:05:14,800
Does she have any friends or
relatives other than you guys?

71
00:05:17,967 --> 00:05:19,533
I know someone.

72
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:43,000
Hello, Astrid.

73
00:05:43,067 --> 00:05:44,267
Hello, Olive.

74
00:05:44,333 --> 00:05:45,833
How are you guys doing?

75
00:05:45,900 --> 00:05:47,100
Not good.

76
00:05:48,300 --> 00:05:50,933
I need you to get me more
Canixidol.

77
00:05:51,967 --> 00:05:53,400
Are you sure?

78
00:05:53,467 --> 00:05:56,433
Don't you think you're taking
this too far, Olive?

79
00:05:56,500 --> 00:06:01,233
You know me, I will do
anything for my daughter.

80
00:06:02,933 --> 00:06:05,100
So, what time can you come over?

81
00:06:05,167 --> 00:06:06,100
Okay.

82
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:11,700
But won't I get followed?

83
00:06:11,767 --> 00:06:14,167
Then you have to be careful.

84
00:06:14,233 --> 00:06:19,033
Make sure that no one follows
you or sees you.

85
00:06:20,267 --> 00:06:21,500
I'll wait for you.

86
00:06:29,267 --> 00:06:32,233
Excuse me, I'll be right back.

87
00:06:37,700 --> 00:06:39,133
Jade, Mom.

88
00:06:39,200 --> 00:06:40,733
Can you stay here?

89
00:06:42,267 --> 00:06:47,667
I'll go with her, Mom.

90
00:06:47,733 --> 00:06:50,433
Okay, I'll handle things here.

91
00:06:50,500 --> 00:06:53,700
Just call us if ever you have
an update.

92
00:06:53,767 --> 00:06:55,000
Be safe.

93
00:06:55,067 --> 00:06:56,533
Okay, Mom.

94
00:07:10,033 --> 00:07:12,267
I hope they can find Mookie.

95
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:15,900
And I hope they won't get
to the point where they have

96
00:07:17,067 --> 00:07:19,133
to kill each other.

97
00:07:20,667 --> 00:07:24,133
If I can only put a stop
to all this mess.

98
00:07:41,933 --> 00:07:43,833
Relax, Mookie.

99
00:07:44,833 --> 00:07:47,767
I'm just going to prepare
for our trip to heaven.

100
00:07:48,867 --> 00:07:50,733
It will all be over soon.

101
00:07:53,967 --> 00:07:55,033
What?

102
00:07:55,100 --> 00:07:57,000
Are you saying something?

103
00:07:59,700 --> 00:08:02,133
You don't want us to go
to heaven.

104
00:08:03,700 --> 00:08:06,500
You want us to go to hell!

105
00:08:08,700 --> 00:08:10,433
You're right, Mookie.

106
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:15,967
Because bad girls go to hell.

107
00:08:17,667 --> 00:08:23,433
And since you have been a
bad girl because you lied to me,

108
00:08:23,533 --> 00:08:25,800
and you betrayed me...

109
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:30,800
Then you must be going to hell.

110
00:08:32,767 --> 00:08:34,167
So, if I were you,

111
00:08:35,700 --> 00:08:38,900
start praying.

112
00:08:38,967 --> 00:08:44,733
And confess all your sins.

113
00:09:10,967 --> 00:09:11,700
Astrid,

114
00:09:12,733 --> 00:09:13,900
- Astrid!
- Emma.

115
00:09:13,967 --> 00:09:17,000
Wait, where's Olive and Mookie?

116
00:09:17,067 --> 00:09:19,233
I don't know what you're talking
about. I'm busy.

117
00:09:19,300 --> 00:09:20,933
Tell us the truth!

118
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:22,867
Where did Olive take Mookie?

119
00:09:22,933 --> 00:09:24,433
I don't know!

120
00:09:26,533 --> 00:09:28,967
We were just at the precinct.

121
00:09:29,067 --> 00:09:30,800
We report Olive's whereabouts.

122
00:09:30,867 --> 00:09:32,800
And if you keep lying to us,

123
00:09:32,867 --> 00:09:35,400
I won't hesitate to file a case
against you, too!

124
00:09:41,933 --> 00:09:43,567
I said I don't know anything!

125
00:09:43,633 --> 00:09:44,733
Wait a minute, what is that?

126
00:09:44,800 --> 00:09:47,833
Give that back! Stop!

127
00:09:49,900 --> 00:09:51,167
What is this?

128
00:09:51,233 --> 00:09:53,433
Are you going to use this
on my daughter?

129
00:09:53,500 --> 00:09:56,733
Are you being paranoid?
Give that back.

130
00:09:56,800 --> 00:09:57,967
You monsters!

131
00:09:58,033 --> 00:09:59,567
I don't know anything!

132
00:09:59,633 --> 00:10:04,067
But to satisfy your curiosity,
this stuff is for my friend.

133
00:10:04,167 --> 00:10:07,833
So you can threaten me all you
want or go live on social media.

134
00:10:07,900 --> 00:10:09,533
I have nothing to do with her!

135
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:11,200
I don't believe you!
Give that to me!

136
00:10:11,267 --> 00:10:13,367
- Give it up, Astrid!
- Give that to me!

137
00:10:13,433 --> 00:10:14,933
Emma!

138
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:15,567
Emma!

139
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:19,433
- Dan, we must follow her.
- Okay, come on.

140
00:10:33,167 --> 00:10:36,033
Danilo, don't ever lose sight
of her.

141
00:10:36,133 --> 00:10:38,533
- Follow her.
- Okay, I got you.

142
00:10:43,533 --> 00:10:45,233
This white van got in the way.

143
00:10:45,300 --> 00:10:46,267
Dan, follow her!

144
00:10:46,333 --> 00:10:47,133
Okay, I will.

145
00:10:47,200 --> 00:10:49,300
We can't lose Mookie.

146
00:11:02,567 --> 00:11:04,300
Dan, where did she go?

147
00:11:04,367 --> 00:11:06,467
Astrid got away.

148
00:11:06,533 --> 00:11:07,767
I lost her.

149
00:11:07,867 --> 00:11:09,133
I'm gonna go on live streaming.

150
00:11:13,467 --> 00:11:16,000
Hello, everyone.

151
00:11:16,067 --> 00:11:18,100
I'm Emma Joseco.

152
00:11:18,167 --> 00:11:20,800
I'm Mookie's real mom.

153
00:11:20,867 --> 00:11:23,967
Olive Caparas kidnapped
my daughter.

154
00:11:24,033 --> 00:11:26,300
If anyone has seen Mookie,

155
00:11:26,367 --> 00:11:31,233
I'm begging you to please
message me in this account.

156
00:11:31,300 --> 00:11:34,567
Help me find my Mookie.

157
00:11:34,633 --> 00:11:36,800
I miss her so much.

158
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:49,600
Is that Canixidol?

159
00:11:49,667 --> 00:11:50,700
Yes, Ma'am.

160
00:11:50,767 --> 00:11:51,733
How come you brought this here
and not Astrid?

161
00:11:51,800 --> 00:11:53,700
Ma'am Astrid asked me
to bring this here

162
00:11:53,767 --> 00:11:55,067
because she had almost gotten
followed.

163
00:11:55,133 --> 00:11:56,733
Good thing she got to lead them
astray.

164
00:11:58,867 --> 00:12:01,833
- Okay.
- Mommy, please! Let me go!

165
00:12:01,900 --> 00:12:03,600
Is that Mookie?

166
00:12:05,833 --> 00:12:07,267
You can go now.

167
00:12:30,600 --> 00:12:32,300
Isn't that Olive?

168
00:12:32,367 --> 00:12:34,033
She's the lady from Maricon's
vlog.

169
00:12:37,367 --> 00:12:39,300
All they said was they were
praying for us

170
00:12:39,367 --> 00:12:40,633
and wishing us well.

171
00:12:41,833 --> 00:12:44,567
No one has seen her yet.

172
00:12:44,633 --> 00:12:47,467
Give it time, Emma.
Someone might help us out.

173
00:12:55,133 --> 00:12:57,433
Dan, someone texted me
an address.

174
00:12:57,500 --> 00:13:00,667
I know where Mookie is.
Let's go get her.

175
00:13:09,700 --> 00:13:12,500
I'm sure this is the place.
I saw the car outside earlier.

176
00:13:12,567 --> 00:13:14,467
Don't even try it!

177
00:13:17,133 --> 00:13:19,433
- Dan.
- Wait.

178
00:13:19,500 --> 00:13:21,500
Don't worry, Mookie.

179
00:13:21,600 --> 00:13:23,900
This will be over soon.

180
00:13:25,767 --> 00:13:26,667
Mommy.

181
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:32,800
I just want to let you know that
if I ever die today,

182
00:13:32,867 --> 00:13:36,200
I love Emma and not you.

183
00:13:40,633 --> 00:13:41,467
- Mookie!
- Shut up!
Emma!

184
00:13:43,233 --> 00:13:44,467
Emma!

185
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:48,433
- What the hell!
- Mommy Emma!

186
00:13:48,500 --> 00:13:50,467
Mom, I'm here!

187
00:13:50,533 --> 00:13:52,567
- Mookie!
- I told you to shut up!

188
00:13:55,233 --> 00:14:00,467
Mom, I'm here! Mom!

189
00:14:07,733 --> 00:14:09,567
Mom!

190
00:14:09,633 --> 00:14:13,033
Very good, Caloy.

191
00:14:13,100 --> 00:14:15,100
You finally did something right.

192
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:20,633
You see, Mookie?

193
00:14:22,167 --> 00:14:26,567
That's what happens to people
who try to meddle with my plans.

194
00:14:28,500 --> 00:14:31,500
They deserve to die!

195
00:14:31,567 --> 00:14:35,567
Mommy, please, stop this.

196
00:14:38,333 --> 00:14:39,900
Relax, Mookie.

197
00:14:42,200 --> 00:14:45,300
This will be over soon.

198
00:14:45,367 --> 00:14:49,967
- We will be together at last.
- No. No, no!

199
00:14:50,033 --> 00:14:53,800
- Forever.
- No, no!

200
00:14:56,267 --> 00:14:58,033
Great idea!

201
00:14:59,267 --> 00:15:00,867
I'll be right back.

202
00:15:03,633 --> 00:15:07,967
Mommy, please! Stop it, please.

203
00:15:12,767 --> 00:15:14,933
Killing you is not in my job
description.

204
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:17,500
But I will do it if you mess
with me!

205
00:15:17,567 --> 00:15:19,233
- You got it?
- Go on!

206
00:15:19,300 --> 00:15:21,233
Don't hurt my wife.

207
00:15:21,300 --> 00:15:22,367
What?

208
00:15:22,433 --> 00:15:25,267
We can make an agreement,
I'll charge you per head!

209
00:15:25,333 --> 00:15:26,733
Go on, hurry up!

210
00:15:28,533 --> 00:15:29,267
Dan!

211
00:15:30,600 --> 00:15:32,167
Dan!

212
00:15:32,233 --> 00:15:34,433
I'm back!

213
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:37,233
Let's get this party started!

214
00:15:39,400 --> 00:15:40,633
Mookie!

215
00:15:47,033 --> 00:15:48,233
Are you ready?

216
00:15:50,067 --> 00:15:52,567
Mommy, what's going on with you?

217
00:15:52,633 --> 00:15:55,600
You're not a killer.

218
00:15:55,667 --> 00:15:58,167
Do you want to go to prison?

219
00:15:58,233 --> 00:16:01,700
I don't plan to get caught
alive!

220
00:16:04,633 --> 00:16:09,033
As a matter of fact,
I don't want to go on living.

221
00:16:11,067 --> 00:16:15,200
If I have to live without you,
Mookie.

222
00:16:16,433 --> 00:16:18,400
Are you okay?

223
00:16:18,467 --> 00:16:20,200
I've come to terms.

224
00:16:21,767 --> 00:16:26,433
That even if I take you away
over and over.

225
00:16:28,367 --> 00:16:32,033
You'll go back to them whenever
you get a chance.

226
00:16:36,867 --> 00:16:40,000
I wanted to be gentle with you,
Mookie.

227
00:16:42,400 --> 00:16:47,133
I don't want you to feel pain
and suffering.

228
00:16:49,167 --> 00:16:50,400
But don't worry...

229
00:16:55,500 --> 00:17:00,267
We'll leave this world together.

230
00:17:01,700 --> 00:17:03,167
No, Mommy.

231
00:17:20,100 --> 00:17:21,567
Emma!

232
00:17:21,633 --> 00:17:22,833
Go!

233
00:17:39,333 --> 00:17:40,433
Mookie!

234
00:17:45,900 --> 00:17:47,200
Mookie, sweetie!

235
00:17:47,267 --> 00:17:48,900
I'm here now, sweetie!

236
00:17:50,400 --> 00:17:51,567
Mom!

237
00:17:51,633 --> 00:17:53,433
Mom!

238
00:17:53,500 --> 00:17:56,833
That meddler is always messing
with my plans!

239
00:17:56,900 --> 00:17:58,000
Mookie!

240
00:17:58,067 --> 00:18:02,000
God, please save my family.

241
00:18:02,067 --> 00:18:03,367
Mookie!

242
00:18:07,533 --> 00:18:08,567
Mom!

243
00:18:12,400 --> 00:18:14,000
Here, there you go.

244
00:18:15,467 --> 00:18:17,667
Don't you ever say a thing.

245
00:18:17,733 --> 00:18:20,567
Or else I will hurt Emma.

246
00:18:20,633 --> 00:18:22,133
Do you understand?

247
00:18:37,233 --> 00:18:38,167
Mookie?

248
00:18:47,033 --> 00:18:47,700
Mookie!

249
00:18:49,533 --> 00:18:52,967
Mookie!

250
00:18:53,033 --> 00:18:55,933
Sweetie!

251
00:18:56,033 --> 00:18:59,600
I'm here now.
You're safe now, sweetie.

252
00:19:05,100 --> 00:19:05,867
Hello, Mom.

253
00:19:05,933 --> 00:19:08,833
We need your help
to find Mookie.

254
00:19:08,900 --> 00:19:11,633
I'll explain later.

255
00:19:11,700 --> 00:19:14,567
Please tell the police officers
to come to this address.

256
00:19:14,633 --> 00:19:15,967
I will send you the details.

257
00:19:16,033 --> 00:19:17,733
I'll send you a text. Okay.

258
00:19:23,067 --> 00:19:25,367
- Mom, hurry!
- Sweetie.

259
00:19:31,367 --> 00:19:33,767
- Mom, hurry!
- Sweetie.

260
00:19:40,800 --> 00:19:41,933
Stop this!

261
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:43,200
Stop right now!

262
00:19:44,333 --> 00:19:46,500
You can never take my daughter
away from me!

263
00:19:49,533 --> 00:19:50,833
Go on!

264
00:19:50,900 --> 00:19:52,133
What are you going to do?

265
00:19:52,200 --> 00:19:54,900
No one will leave this room!

266
00:19:54,967 --> 00:19:56,967
Now that we're all here.

267
00:19:57,767 --> 00:19:59,833
- Mommy, no!
- Olive, that's enough!

268
00:19:59,900 --> 00:20:01,933
- Mommy! Stop it!
- We can all die here!

269
00:20:02,033 --> 00:20:02,967
Stop it!

270
00:20:05,967 --> 00:20:08,833
Mommy, please!
What is going on with you?

271
00:20:11,267 --> 00:20:14,800
If I can't have my daughter
forever!

272
00:20:14,867 --> 00:20:17,567
We can all die!

273
00:20:18,700 --> 00:20:22,167
Mommy, please.

274
00:20:22,233 --> 00:20:24,367
No one is replying.

275
00:20:24,433 --> 00:20:26,300
Ligaya hasn't replied yet.

276
00:20:26,367 --> 00:20:28,400
I wonder what happened
to Mookie.

277
00:20:28,467 --> 00:20:31,333
My hemorrhoids are popping out
from all this stress!

278
00:20:31,400 --> 00:20:33,367
Let's go ask the guard.

279
00:20:33,433 --> 00:20:34,967
They might know where they are.

280
00:20:35,067 --> 00:20:37,400
Excuse me, do you happen to know
Mookie?

281
00:20:37,467 --> 00:20:39,300
I'm also looking for her.

282
00:20:39,367 --> 00:20:41,400
We're Mookie's grandmother's
best friends.

283
00:20:41,467 --> 00:20:43,900
We're also friends
with her parents.

284
00:20:43,967 --> 00:20:46,033
What about you?
How did you know her?

285
00:20:46,100 --> 00:20:47,733
I'm Mookie's friend.

286
00:20:47,800 --> 00:20:49,200
My name is Zayn, by the way.

287
00:20:49,267 --> 00:20:51,567
What a handsome boy!

288
00:20:51,633 --> 00:20:54,100
I like you for Mookie.

289
00:20:54,167 --> 00:20:55,500
My name is Wiro.

290
00:20:55,567 --> 00:20:59,100
- I'm Zayn. Nice to meet you.
- And I'm Kutsy.

291
00:20:59,167 --> 00:21:01,000
Do you want to come with me?

292
00:21:01,067 --> 00:21:02,933
I have a car.

293
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:06,233
Rich kid. Of course, as long as
I sit in the front.

294
00:21:06,300 --> 00:21:11,100
Come on, let's go ask
that guard.

295
00:21:11,200 --> 00:21:12,633
What a flirt.

296
00:21:12,700 --> 00:21:14,800
- Okay.
- Hurry up.

297
00:21:34,267 --> 00:21:34,967
Mookie.

298
00:21:35,033 --> 00:21:36,967
Please, Mommy.

299
00:21:37,033 --> 00:21:38,400
Please.

300
00:21:38,467 --> 00:21:39,767
Mommy, please.

301
00:21:39,833 --> 00:21:41,400
Don't do it, Olive.

302
00:21:41,500 --> 00:21:43,067
- Hey! No!
- Dan!

303
00:21:43,133 --> 00:21:44,967
- Let me go! Come on.
- Dan

304
00:21:48,867 --> 00:21:50,467
Let me go!

305
00:21:50,533 --> 00:21:51,733
Come on.

306
00:22:00,033 --> 00:22:00,667
Upstairs!
That's Emma.

307
00:22:01,700 --> 00:22:03,933
Come on, let's go upstairs!
Over here.

308
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:06,167
I won't let you hurt my family!

309
00:22:06,233 --> 00:22:07,833
Let me go!

310
00:22:15,200 --> 00:22:16,000
What now!

311
00:22:16,067 --> 00:22:18,000
What!

312
00:22:18,067 --> 00:22:20,133
You can't take my daughter
away from me!

313
00:22:21,300 --> 00:22:22,167
Stop!

314
00:22:24,133 --> 00:22:27,567
No! Don't hurt her!

315
00:22:28,600 --> 00:22:30,600
You shouldn't fight like this!

316
00:22:31,633 --> 00:22:33,333
You and Emma are sisters!

317
00:22:52,900 --> 00:22:54,833
What are you talking about?

318
00:22:55,800 --> 00:22:58,467
What do you mean,
Emma is my sister?

319
00:22:58,533 --> 00:23:00,533
It's true, Olive.

320
00:23:03,033 --> 00:23:07,433
You were the twin that I gave up
for adoption before.

321
00:23:14,267 --> 00:23:16,100
I'm your biological mother.

322
00:23:27,433 --> 00:23:30,367
No! No!

323
00:23:30,433 --> 00:23:33,467
I don't believe you,
you old hag!

324
00:23:33,533 --> 00:23:36,000
You're just messing
with my head!

325
00:23:36,067 --> 00:23:39,000
To stop me from hurting you!

326
00:23:39,067 --> 00:23:43,833
No, I won't believe your lies!

327
00:23:43,900 --> 00:23:45,167
Listen to me, dear.

328
00:23:45,233 --> 00:23:46,300
Listen.

329
00:23:47,767 --> 00:23:50,567
When I spent some time with
Jade,

330
00:23:50,633 --> 00:23:53,067
I learned the truth about you.

331
00:23:53,133 --> 00:23:55,967
You were my twin.

332
00:23:56,067 --> 00:23:57,967
You have to believe me.

333
00:24:02,900 --> 00:24:06,433
No, I don't believe you.

334
00:24:06,500 --> 00:24:10,167
No! No!

335
00:24:13,667 --> 00:24:15,167
That's not true.

336
00:24:15,233 --> 00:24:18,367
She's telling the truth, Olive.

337
00:24:24,133 --> 00:24:25,033
This.

338
00:24:26,800 --> 00:24:30,133
This is proof that she's our
biological mother.

339
00:24:31,533 --> 00:24:33,700
You have one of these too,
don't you?

340
00:24:35,000 --> 00:24:36,633
But you throw yours away

341
00:24:36,700 --> 00:24:39,067
because you're furious
about our mother.

342
00:24:42,333 --> 00:24:45,700
Ligaya gave this to our
adoptive parents

343
00:24:45,767 --> 00:24:47,867
before she gave us up
for adoption.

344
00:24:54,500 --> 00:24:55,667
Look at this picture.

345
00:24:58,500 --> 00:25:02,833
Our lawyer gave this to us
when our parents died.

346
00:25:04,900 --> 00:25:07,933
And the letter behind this
picture...

347
00:25:11,067 --> 00:25:13,633
Ligaya wrote it.

348
00:25:17,367 --> 00:25:20,067
No! No!

349
00:25:31,633 --> 00:25:32,967
Miss Caparas!

350
00:25:33,033 --> 00:25:34,767
You have to surrender now!

351
00:25:34,833 --> 00:25:38,767
Mom, if Mommy asked you
for forgiveness

352
00:25:38,867 --> 00:25:41,500
and changed her ways.

353
00:25:41,567 --> 00:25:43,833
Will you forgive her?

354
00:25:43,900 --> 00:25:46,600
Even though she's my sister.

355
00:25:46,667 --> 00:25:49,933
She still did you wrong.

356
00:25:50,000 --> 00:25:51,333
No.

357
00:25:51,400 --> 00:25:52,900
Officers!

358
00:25:52,967 --> 00:25:54,400
She's here!

359
00:25:54,467 --> 00:25:56,367
She has to pay
for her wrongdoings.

360
00:25:56,433 --> 00:26:00,267
I said, let me go!
You can't detain me!

361
00:26:00,333 --> 00:26:05,067
No matter what you do, you still
can't escape all your sins.

362
00:26:05,133 --> 00:26:06,533
I have a lot of money!

363
00:26:06,600 --> 00:26:08,300
I can do anything I want!

364
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:11,067
Wait for me to get out
of here...

365
00:26:11,133 --> 00:26:13,267
You'll see what I can do, Emma!
